  18 def param_type_complete(self, ctx, incomplete):
  19     """Returns a set of possible completions values, along with their documentation string
  20 
  21     Default implementation of the complete method for click.types.ParamType just returns an empty list
  22 
  23     Parameters
  24     ----------
  25     ctx : click.core.Context
  26         The current context
  27     incomplete :
  28         The string to complete
  29 
  30     Returns
  31     -------
  32     [(str, str)]
  33         A list of completion results. The first element of each tuple is actually the argument to complete, the second
  34         element is an help string for this argument.
  35     """
  36     return []
  37 
  38 
  39 def choice_complete(self, ctx, incomplete):
  40     """Returns the completion results for click.core.Choice
  41 
  42     Parameters
  43     ----------
  44     ctx : click.core.Context
  45         The current context
  46     incomplete :
  47         The string to complete
  48 
  49     Returns
  50     -------
  51     [(str, str)]
  52         A list of completion results
  53     """
  54     return [
  55         (c, None) for c in self.choices
  56         if completion_configuration.match_incomplete(c, incomplete)
  57     ]
  58

  60 def multicommand_get_command_short_help(self, ctx, cmd_name):
  61     """Returns the short help of a subcommand
  62 
  63     It allows MultiCommand subclasses to implement more efficient ways to provide the subcommand short help, for
  64     example by leveraging some caching.
  65 
  66     Parameters
  67     ----------
  68     ctx : click.core.Context
  69         The current context
  70     cmd_name :
  71         The sub command name
  72 
  73     Returns
  74     -------
  75     str
  76         The sub command short help
  77     """
  78     return self.get_command(ctx, cmd_name).get_short_help_str()
  79 
  80 
  81 def multicommand_get_command_hidden(self, ctx, cmd_name):
  82     """Returns the short help of a subcommand
  83 
  84     It allows MultiCommand subclasses to implement more efficient ways to provide the subcommand hidden attribute, for
  85     example by leveraging some caching.
  86 
  87     Parameters
  88     ----------
  89     ctx : click.core.Context
  90         The current context
  91     cmd_name :
  92         The sub command name
  93 
  94     Returns
  95     -------
  96     bool
  97         The sub command hidden status
  98     """
  99     cmd = self.get_command(ctx, cmd_name)
 100     return cmd.hidden if cmd else False

 103 def _shellcomplete(cli, prog_name, complete_var=None):
 104     """Internal handler for the bash completion support.
 105 
 106     Parameters
 107     ----------
 108     cli : click.Command
 109         The main click Command of the program
 110     prog_name : str
 111         The program name on the command line
 112     complete_var : str
 113         The environment variable name used to control the completion behavior (Default value = None)
 114     """
 115     if complete_var is None:
 116         complete_var = '_%s_COMPLETE' % (prog_name.replace('-', '_')).upper()
 117     complete_instr = os.environ.get(complete_var)
 118     if not complete_instr:
 119         return
 120 
 121     if complete_instr == 'source':
 122         echo(get_code(prog_name=prog_name, env_name=complete_var))
 123     elif complete_instr == 'source-bash':
 124         echo(get_code('bash', prog_name, complete_var))
 125     elif complete_instr == 'source-fish':
 126         echo(get_code('fish', prog_name, complete_var))
 127     elif complete_instr == 'source-powershell':
 128         echo(get_code('powershell', prog_name, complete_var))
 129     elif complete_instr == 'source-zsh':
 130         echo(get_code('zsh', prog_name, complete_var))
 131     elif complete_instr in ['complete', 'complete-bash']:
 132         # keep 'complete' for bash for backward compatibility
 133         do_bash_complete(cli, prog_name)
 134     elif complete_instr == 'complete-fish':
 135         do_fish_complete(cli, prog_name)
 136     elif complete_instr == 'complete-powershell':
 137         do_powershell_complete(cli, prog_name)
 138     elif complete_instr == 'complete-zsh':
 139         do_zsh_complete(cli, prog_name)
 140     elif complete_instr == 'install':
 141         shell, path = install(prog_name=prog_name, env_name=complete_var)
 142         click.echo('%s completion installed in %s' % (shell, path))
 143     elif complete_instr == 'install-bash':
 144         shell, path = install(shell='bash', prog_name=prog_name, env_name=complete_var)
 145         click.echo('%s completion installed in %s' % (shell, path))
 146     elif complete_instr == 'install-fish':
 147         shell, path = install(shell='fish', prog_name=prog_name, env_name=complete_var)
 148         click.echo('%s completion installed in %s' % (shell, path))
 149     elif complete_instr == 'install-zsh':
 150         shell, path = install(shell='zsh', prog_name=prog_name, env_name=complete_var)
 151         click.echo('%s completion installed in %s' % (shell, path))
 152     elif complete_instr == 'install-powershell':
 153         shell, path = install(shell='powershell', prog_name=prog_name, env_name=complete_var)
 154         click.echo('%s completion installed in %s' % (shell, path))
 155     sys.exit()
 156 
 157 
 158 def patch():
 159     """Patch click"""
 160     import click
 161     click.types.ParamType.complete = param_type_complete
 162     click.types.Choice.complete = choice_complete
 163     click.core.MultiCommand.get_command_short_help = multicommand_get_command_short_help
 164     click.core.MultiCommand.get_command_hidden = multicommand_get_command_hidden
 165     click.core._bashcomplete = _shellcomplete
